  "description": [
    "FEDERAL LAW ON CHILD LABOR GIVEN SUPPORT Most boys play marbles and most girls play with dolls but 1060856 children between the ages of 10 and 15thats one child in every twelve never get the chance They are the little toilers in the mills the mines the factories and the fields to whose plight the Na tional Child Labor Committee and the U S Childrens Bureau is call ing nationwide attention on Jan Behind it all is an 26 27 and 28 effort to get thru Congress a con stitutional amendment which will give Congress the power to pass a federal child labor law that will stick Unconstitutional There is now no federal law ap plying to child labor Two such at tempts by Congress have failed both laws being knocked out by the U S Supreme Court as being un constitutional The average percentage among eracy among all children between 10 and 15 in the U S is 23 in some of the big child labor sections the percentage of illiteracy suns more than 14 per cent The averabe percentage among the population of 10 years and over is 6 per cent but in the big child labor states"
  ],
